included.description: The Experience Architecture club was founded by a fellow student, myself and 2 others. The goal of the club is to allow fellow Experience Architecture majors to get to know one another while also providing resources to prepare them for a job outside of college. To achieve this, myself and the president organize workshops for resumes and portfolios while also inviting professionals from the surrounding area in to speak about their careers.

included.companyName: College of Arts and Letters - Michigan State University
included.description: As an accessibility intern through the College of Arts and Letters, I work with faculty to ensure their courses and websites are in line with laws regarding accessibility and education. I comb through each course and website under the college to ensure it is WCAG 2.0 compliant by using screen readers as well as other development tools. Using these tools we can pinpoint errors and offer suggestions on how best to remediate.
included.title: Web Accessibility Intern

included.companyName: Michigan State University College of Arts and Letters
included.description: I set out to determine why Learning Management Systems, specifically those for higher education, had such a negative connotation associated to them. I have used more than 5 different systems and have yet to find one that offers a great experience while also being fully accessible to those with disabilities. This project included learning management research, user surveys, high and low content wireframes and full-fledged designs. The project resulted in a talk at an Accessible Learning Conference at MSU.

included.title: Project Manager

included.description: As a user experience analyst, I am tasked with researching our users through various analytic tracking platforms, synthesizing information in a way that can be understood and processed by all, developing easy-to-use web tools for our internal team members, prioritizing new features with our dedicated technology team, and conducting focus groups and shadowing sessions with both high and low usage users.
included.title: User Experience Analyst

included.summary: As a user experience architect, I am interested in and passionate about web design, web development, accessibility and overall usability. These interests allow me to be creative in my projects while also being empathetic to those that will be using the end product. A great product is both great to look at and easy to use. I have worked on projects both individually and collaboratively that meet these exact goals.

Alongside several Quicken Loans team members and Veterans of the United States Military, we designed and built a small park in an underdeveloped area of Detroit. The park included two wood benches, a gazebo, and several local plants all over top a layer of rock and mulch. We designed and built this park on one of the hottest days of the summer to help develop an area of Detroit the government hasn't gotten to yet.

Every week for two nights I would tutor underpriveleged children throughout the Lansing community through a program called Read to Succeed. This program was based on reading and writing though if students needed special help on homework in other areas we were there to assist. I worked with one student all semester and was able to see a vast improvement on both reading and writing which was a huge milestone for a kid who started out so far behind in his grade.
